Rating: 4
This is a very authentic-tasting recipe, and easy too; you can make the rice in the morning, put it in the fridge, and it'll come together in less than an hour. We love it; can't wait to try with fresh peas this spring; you might also use corn later in the year, esp. if following another reviewer's suggestion of adding shrimp. But definitely use Spanish-style, not Mexican, chorizo; the former is a drier sausage, and really makes the dish. (See La Tienda.com; get the mild rather than the spicy.) Oh, yes, the garlic, too!

Rating: 3
great use of leftover chinese white rice. used linguica also (less fatty) and stir fried 1lb shrimp. fast delicious dinner- tastes even better next day.

Rating: 4
I saw Sara Moulton cooked this dish on her show called, "Sara Secrets" on the Food Network. Excellent quick dish recipe. I used Linguisa sausage instead of Chorizo (our supermarket did not carry Chorizo sausages). I also substituted 1-1/2 teaspoons ground cumin for the 1 tablespoon cumin seeds (didn't have cumin seeds on hand)and added the ground cumin after browning the onions and red peppers. I also added 2 cloves minced garlic. Omitted the pumpkin seeds, but thinking about subsituting the pumpkin seeds for toasted pine nuts in the future and adding some prawns to the dish as well. Great recipe!

