This dish is a solid start for many things. As a stand alone product I thought it was a little bland. Use your imagination (shrimp, chicken gizzards) and some common sense (tomato sauce, chicken stock) and you can do great things with this basen recipe. Whatever you do, you have to use the old rice.

Rating: 2
1. Great advice given about using older rice! Not too many people share that little secret and new cooks should thank you. 2. What, no seafood in this? Add a few bits of shrimp or grouper,etc. cut to bite-size and sauteed after the sausage. 3. Skip the pumpkin seeds and add 1/3 C. pinenuts toasted with the cumin. 4. Char and peel the red pepper and add near the end. 5. Minced Garlic anyone?